        <h2>Is Sage 100 Contractor right for you?</h2>
        <p><strong>Choose Sage 100 Contractor if:</strong> You're a mid-size contractor ($3M–$50M) who needs integrated accounting and estimating, does prevailing wage or certified payroll work, wants a single system rather than multiple integrated tools, and has budget for proper implementation by a Sage reseller.</p>
        <p><strong>Consider alternatives if:</strong> You're under $2M revenue (Foundation or QuickBooks are better fits), you need strong mobile/field management (pair it with Procore), you're a Mac shop (cloud hosting helps but it's not ideal), or you want a modern SaaS experience (Sage 100 Contractor's UX will frustrate you).</p>

